	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#000000" bordercolor="#000000" class="maintext">
<h1><div align="center">The Scribery</div></h1>
<h3 align="center">ITB Soap Opera</h3>
                               <P><font size="-1">CHANNEL&nbsp;K.A.A.O.S. brings 
                                    you that new laugh riot Soap Opera:<BR>
                                    <I>&quot;As the House Burns&quot;<BR>
                                    </I>Another fine ITB&nbsp;humiliation for 
                                    us all to enjoy!&nbsp; ;D<BR>
                                    <BR>
                                    <I>(If ya got the time, read it all. &nbsp;It's 
                                    quite a lesson in how NOT&nbsp;to act or run 
                                    a guild. &nbsp;<BR>
                                    Even one as lame as ITB.)</I></font></P>
                                  <P>
                                  <hr>
                                </CENTER>
                                <P><font size="-1">Starring:&nbsp;&nbsp;ITB&nbsp;Skorp 
                                  as the paranoid cheerleader of House ITB who 
                                  made the &quot;No NW&nbsp;Staff can ever control 
                                  ITB&quot;, then quickly erased it from the ITB&nbsp;history 
                                  books when he became a Staffer! &nbsp;His strong-armed 
                                  tactis about not allowing anyone to disagree 
                                  with him, has led to &quot;another fine mess&quot; 
                                  for the Itties.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Faust - The angry, 
                                  young rebel, freshly returned from this duties 
                                  overseas, to a House in turmoil, as he finds 
                                  House ITB&nbsp;wallowing in stagnation and mediocrity.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Co-Starring:&nbsp;&nbsp;ITB&nbsp;Teddi 
                                  - The beautiful star of KAAOS' own &quot;A KAAOS&nbsp;Xmas&quot; 
                                  in which she scrubbed her kitty in front of 
                                  thousands of viewers. &nbsp;She stars in this 
                                  Soap as a hanger-on of Skorp. &nbsp;Lord knows 
                                  she never did anything worthwhile by herself.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Smoke - The dimwitted 
                                  truckdriver who is seduced by the power of GM-ship, 
                                  only once he takes the reigns he was heard to 
                                  remark &quot;Hey, this is kinda hard...do I&nbsp;have 
                                  to go in the game and talk to people and stuff, 
                                  now?&quot;</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Arcane - The starry-eyed 
                                  young stud, with visions of the GM-ship in his 
                                  head. But his slow, less than bright coupe de 
                                  'etet plans were shattered when he realized 
                                  he may actually have to POST and TALK now!</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Onyx - The young studly 
                                  ne'erdowell, whose final months in House ITB&nbsp;were 
                                  spent daydreaming about joining KAAOS, while 
                                  sticking around to try and save the &quot;bond&quot; 
                                  one last time. &nbsp;He quits ITB&nbsp;in disgust. 
                                  (Ed note:&nbsp;There goes another one!&nbsp;Heh!&nbsp;&nbsp;Heh!)</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Lilyth - The young 
                                  tem</font><font size="-1">ptress, out to do 
                                  as many NWN'ers as humanly possible. &nbsp;Although 
                                  she'd only do Faust from the&nbsp;House or do 
                                  KAAOS'ers, once she seen the slim pickins she 
                                  had to choose from ITB&nbsp;at the bashes.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Xavier - The goodnatured, 
                                  mildly retarted Amish boy, whose only visions 
                                  of glory were how many names he could make-up 
                                  that he had &quot;killed&quot; during the Wild 
                                  Hunts in Southwall.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Master - The genius 
                                  computer programmer, whose severe handicap of 
                                  not being able to ever spell, caused him to 
                                  start sucking at PVP, and being ignored when 
                                  he tried to post.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Special Guest Appearence:&nbsp;&nbsp;ITB&nbsp;Vortex!&nbsp;&nbsp;House 
                                  ITB's first hacker (yes, even before Gawain!), 
                                  whose acquisition of XGM&nbsp;almost a YEAR 
                                  before it made it's way into mass distribution, 
                                  allowed him to never miss a save on the PVP&nbsp;Ladders! 
                                  &nbsp;He made a brief appearence during the 
                                  SOL/ITB&nbsp;WAR, but he couldn't compete when 
                                  everyone was on a level playing field, so he 
                                  mysteriously disappeared again.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">And without further ado, ladies 
                                  and gentlemen...we have for you, the entire 
                                  script of &quot;As the House Burns&quot;! &nbsp;ENJOY! 
                                  ;)</font></P>
                                <P> 
                                <HR>
                                <font size="-1">From: ITB&nbsp;FAUST </font> 
                                <p></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Subj: A message from Faust<BR>
                                  Date: 97-07-22 05:11:53 EDT<BR>
                                  From: ITB ;&gt;</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Faust asked me to post this 
                                  here for him since he cancelled his AOL account. 
                                  I'll have to admit I'm pretty much in agreement 
                                  with him. I saw what ITB was when I first joined 
                                  and saw what it was becoming before the game 
                                  died. Needless to say for those of you who where 
                                  in the guild roughly 2 1/2 years ago until the 
                                  game died, should know what I am talking about.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">She's right, I'm WAY out of 
                                  touch. I was under the impression that ITB was 
                                  an Evil guild full of uncompromising bad asses 
                                  like Gawain, Lasher, Cormyr, Silent, Bolt and 
                                  all the other guys from our era. I didn't realize 
                                  what its turned into... I'll have to go get 
                                  my wittle stuffy-huggie-bear and sit by the 
                                  fireside wi'v my bwankie and listen to Burl 
                                  Ives tunes on my hand crank music box and get 
                                  huggies from my friends in the bond more often.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Either that or I'm going to 
                                  go out and kick some newbies BUTT and stamp 
                                  on his GUTS until he screams for his mommy and 
                                  when she shows up I'll stuff Jr's leg in her 
                                  mouth and let her eat it while I rip her entrails 
                                  out and strangle her with them! Then I might 
                                  go jaw some loser until he cries and whines 
                                  about my posts for a while.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">I can't figure out which would 
                                  be more fun.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Faust In The (Old) Bond </font>
                                <HR> <p></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Subj: Re:A message from Faust<BR>
                                  Date: 97-07-22 14:19:47 EDT <BR>
                                  From: ITB Smoke </font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">This isnt really the folder 
                                  for this but it was started here.. so I'll respond 
                                  here... Faust is right about what ITB used to 
                                  be... we where a bunch of bad-ass's that didn't 
                                  take dung from anybody.... We used to stand 
                                  up for each other, no mater what.. We where 
                                  ITB first and foremost, the others be damned... 
                                  Now I aint so sure anymore.. I have copy's of 
                                  officer mail that Arcane forwarded to Ravish.. 
                                  I have copy's of that same mail the Ravish forwarded 
                                  to people outside the guild... I wanted to put 
                                  a stop to it then but was &quot;talked out of 
                                  it&quot; by the other officers and elders (dont 
                                  rock the boat)... We have others in the guild 
                                  going &quot;behind our backs&quot; to gather 
                                  support for changes in the Bond... We have sudo-evils 
                                  that cant make up their minds if they want to 
                                  be evil or good...We have people sticking up 
                                  for members, that if it was 3 years ago, would 
                                  of been booted long before without question...</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Well... I'm tired of sitting 
                                  the fence trying to make everyone happy...ITB 
                                  always has been an EVIL guild that stuck together 
                                  and caused <B>havok</B> to the rest of the realms.. 
                                  not <B>havok</B> within. If you want to be a 
                                  part of ITB and join us in the other realms 
                                  as a force who's only aim is kick'n butt on 
                                  outsiders then come with us, our new Web boards 
                                  are waiting for you... If ya want to sit fences.. 
                                  and play your politics... join NOR.. ITB dont 
                                  want ya.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Smoke </font>
                                <HR> <p></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">&gt; From: P Wigutow &lt;pwigutow@lnd.com<BR>
                                  To: 'Faust@primenet.com' &gt;<BR>
                                  Subject: <BR>
                                  Date: Tuesday, July 22, 1997 5:25 PM <BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  And here's my reply to your attacks on Teddi 
                                  and I. That shit is uncalled for, and, I'll 
                                  take it, but, I aint gonna watch you heap it 
                                  on anyone else. <BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Cheers Asshole,<BR>
                                  Skorp<BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Subj: Re:A message from Faust &gt;<BR>
                                  Date: 97-07-22 18:05:44 EDT &gt;<BR>
                                  From: ITB Skorp &gt; <BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Faust was always a ego maniac who did not cried 
                                  and spouted off when he didnt get his way. Ya 
                                  wanna know his idea of how this bond should 
                                  deal with Arc's aspirations to lead the bond...here 
                                  it was...&quot;boot him make a web page defaming 
                                  him&quot;.Gee, thats class. &gt; &gt;<BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Of course, this was within days Faust told me 
                                  that if folks didnt see Smoke as a good leader 
                                  anymore that he would step in and take over 
                                  Smoke's spot.Yes Smoke, at the same time you 
                                  saw him defending you, he tried to convince 
                                  me that HE should take over. &gt; &gt; Of course, 
                                  that idea didnt fly, and, when it did'nt, once 
                                  again, he made his power play by trying to start 
                                  a little inner circle and bad mouthing Arcane, 
                                  Teddi and myself every chance he got. THAT'S 
                                  a bond? Some non-existant self important pompous 
                                  fool who has'nt contributed squat to the guild 
                                  in over two years, and goes around bad mouthing 
                                  folks who are currently running the guild, and, 
                                  while acting on one side to be the biggest supporter 
                                  of Smoke on one hand, is, on the other hand, 
                                  suggesting that HE take over for a while? &gt; 
                                  &gt; <BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Me? Ya, I can be soft at times. Wanna know why? 
                                  Cause...OOC...this is a group of friends who 
                                  are supposed to be having fun together.Thats 
                                  about it. FUN. Yes, we strive to be the best, 
                                  and, to have inspire respect and fear, but, 
                                  running around playing little power games aint 
                                  what it is about. Folks say I &quot;Politic&quot;...well..maybe 
                                  thats the way you see it, I see it as peacemaking.After 
                                  all, ya can be evil without being a jerk...but...those 
                                  who are natural jerks wouldnt understand that. 
                                  &gt; &gt;<BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Tell ya what folks, let the people decied this 
                                  one, cause I for one am not going to put up 
                                  with being slammed, and having two good friends 
                                  who have done everything they can to promote 
                                  the guild be back stabbed, by someone who calls 
                                  these kinds of actions the way of &quot;The 
                                  Bond&quot; &gt; &gt; Boot Fausts ass now, or, 
                                  choose to keep him...yer choice, but, if his 
                                  kind of Bond is what you want, then count Me 
                                  and Teddi out of it.<BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Skorp</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1"><B>(Ed Note: Notice the &quot;ITB&nbsp;XXXX&nbsp;was 
