                                <P><font size="-1">Forwarded Message:<BR>
                                  Subj: rofl<BR>
                                  Date: 97-07-18 00:56:04 EDT<BR>
                                  From: <BR>
                                  To: </font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Well Kids,</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">I think I'll make my official 
                                  goodbye now. I'll be killing my AOL account 
                                  in the next day or two and then its off to the 
                                  great beyond. I thought about chastizing several 
                                  people around here for the recent crap that 
                                  has come up but, in the long run we all know 
                                  who's who, don't we? Someone un Ultima asked 
                                  me to provide a report on the NWN Guilds and 
                                  what they are up to. I'll attach what I said 
                                  about ITB to give you an idea of my thoughts 
                                  and leave it at that.</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">So, up with the boot straps 
                                  and I'm out there somewhere. Those of you who 
                                  need a hand with UO feel free to give me a call. 
                                  I'm on ICQ and Email and all that stuff. For 
                                  those of you that I'll see again, Lets hope 
                                  we see each other soon!. For those of you who 
                                  I WON'T see again, it was a pleasure to know 
                                  you and I'll always have fond memories of my 
                                  time in the best house in Neverwinter...</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB Faust / ITB Drunk Always 
                                  - In The Bond - Take It! -</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">_____________________________________</font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">Report to Ultima: ITB (In The 
                                  Bond) - My former home in Neverwinter and still 
                                  a close tie. A group reputed for Pkilling and 
                                  exceptional organization in Neverwinter since 
                                  its inception in 1992. Massive organizational 
                                  abilities and aggressive instincts give these 
                                  guys a reputation bar none in NWN communities. 
                                  This guild can easily operate on name alone 
                                  and MOST of the Pkillers in the game pay a great 
                                  deal of attention to them. <BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  For several years the guild was essentially 
                                  the monsters most challenging to kill and people 
                                  dreamed of one day either becoming or beating 
                                  them. Everyone (at one time) wanted to be an 
                                  ITB and only the best could get in. Once this 
                                  policy changed the guild started going down 
                                  hill. Currently this guild is more concerned 
                                  with internal strife involving a fight over 
                                  power and a lot of personnel problems concerning 
                                  old leaders who cannot give it up and young 
                                  members who don't know the first thing about 
                                  how to run a guild. There are very good people 
                                  here though. Exceptionally skill and adaptive 
                                  players. One is writing his own video game and 
                                  that takes all his time. The current GM (Guild 
                                  Master) is a former truck driver who used to 
                                  show up in everyone's home town from time to 
                                  time drawing us all into a tight group of friends. 
                                  Another former leader is so far up the butt 
                                  of all the current and former staffers in NW 
                                  that he knows just about everything about everyone.... 
                                  he is, however, somewhat delusional about his 
                                  popularity.&nbsp;(Ed. note:&nbsp;ROFL!!) One 
                                  is a staff member at Lucas Art's, a game manufacturer.<BR>
                                  <BR>
                                  Another proposed a revolt to throw out the 10 
                                  top (eldest) members a little while ago sending 
                                  the guild into a huge tailspin ending only because 
                                  NWN was announced as closing.<BR>
                                  This situation prevails in the current mentality 
                                  of the guild and divisions are insufferable 
                                  in such a group. Lots of these people (the guild 
                                  membership) are, in one way or another, being 
                                  demoralized because of the internal strife and, 
                                  quite frankly, I don't see an end to it given 
                                  the personalities involved. As these people 
                                  become more and more alienated they will begin 
                                  to break off and look for independent homes. 
                                  I have notified every one of them that despite 
                                  previous political adversity I would make them 
                                  at home in whatever capacity possible here in 
                                  UO. This might involve you and my &quot;team&quot; 
                                  or it might not, we'll wait and see what the 
                                  individual wants. I feel I should let you know 
                                  that I will go way out of my way to assist any 
                                  ITB requesting my assistance (without breaking 
                                  certain confidences of course) No news concerning 
                                  an &quot;official move&quot; to Ultima Online 
                                  and they might be going to another game anyway 
                                  as NWN shuts down. </font></P>
                                <P><font size="-1">ITB&nbsp;Faust 		</td>
